And when the stimulus check money runs dry, Americans will be plunged deeper into debt.
The student loan debt of $1.6 trillion, the medical debt of $88 billion wrecked lives; it could have been paid off.
Over 3 million Americans filed for unemployment in March, and in April it could be tens of millions.
After medical treatment, 137 million Americans face severe debt.
The new poor joined the 93.6 million who scrape by on low incomes; the 38.1 million poor in 2018 that include 17 million in deep poverty.